description:
Giving Nature A Voice - Season 2, Episode 1: Plastics Are Forever | Nature Documentary

Kenya’s marine life is increasingly choked by plastic debris. Flip-flops, plastic bottles and nets clutter the white sand beaches, entangling and  killing marine animals, birds and fish. In Watamu, local clean up crews collect the plastic and sort it for re-use.
In Malindi, a recycling plant turns the waste into sidewalks, street signs and even beams for an experimental dhow under construction in Lamu. Will the world’s strictest ban on plastic bags begin to turn the tide that's cluttering our coastline?

You will see fascinating shots from the deep seas and up in the air, capturing great stories and pictures from everything our beautiful and interesting planet has to offer. 

Enjoy stories about nature, wildlife, culture, people, history and more to come.
